  <exercise>
    <title>c</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Use the vectors \mathbf{v} and \mathbf{w} below to give a geometric representation of the vector which is the sum <m>\vect{v}+\vect{w}</m>.
        If this interpretation is applied to \mathbf{w}+\mathbf{v} is the result the same?
        If this interpretation is applied to <m>(\vect{v} +\vect{w}) + \vect{u}</m> and
        <m>\vect{v} + ( \vect{w} + \vect{u})</m> are those results the same?
